<DOCNO> AP901007-0006 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
his presumed ideology has been condemned on 
all sides his housekeeping has been derided and his neckties have 
been likened to dishrags but david souters friends say he is a 
man content with himself who wont change when he joins the supreme 
court this week 
goodness no thats like saying that gibraltar could be 
changed by a rainstorm said sen warren rudman rnh who 
preceded souter as state attorney general and sat behind him all 
through senate confirmation hearings 
david souters foundations and values have been built over 51 
years rudman said david hasnt changed at all and will not 
change at all 
the 51yearold ascetic bachelors life has been turned upside 
down in the past few months as he went from a littleknown regional 
jurist to one of the nations nine most powerful judges 
liberals and conservatives alike have voiced suspicions that 
hell vote against them on abortion civil rights and other social 
issues journalists have scrutinized everything from his suits to 
how hell cope with crime noise and high real estate prices in the 
nations capital 
but friends say he ultimately will be the softspoken 
eventempered man he always has been whether he is in weare nh 
or washington where he moved this weekend to get ready to join the 
court tuesday 
hes in a constant whirl of change but he will be himself 
wherever he is he is satisfied with who he is said concord 
lawyer tom rath souters deputy and successor as attorney general 
throughout a barrage of public and media scrutiny that began 
when president bush nominated him to the court july 23 souter 
remained polite almost courtly to anyone who begged a minute 
no trouble at all he told a apologetic reporter who called 
him at his weare farmhouse the phone number is still in the book 
the day he returned from senate judiciary committee hearings 
thats david souter rudman said he is without a doubt 
one of the most selfeffacing gracious people i have ever met 
but rath noted i think there were moments when that sort of 
basic nature of him good natured unfailingly courteous was 
tested 
some of those moments included an inventory of souters ancient 
kitchen appliances made by reporters peeking through his windows 
while he was in washington meeting senators 
souter joked about it when i think of all the things i should 
have left out if id known somebody was going to peek but ill 
never have that chance again 
in reality he was annoyed rudman and rath said 
he didnt like that and he felt people overstepped their 
bounds but i think he understood that for a few weeks or months 
hed have to endure it rudman said 
rath said friends tried to make sure that souters courtesy 
didnt allow people to take advantage of him 
i got angry a couple of times very angry the first friday he 
got back and he went over to see his mother said rath who 
acted as souters press agent and personal sentry after the 
nomination 
souter he recalled went in the back door of his mothers home 
in a concord retirement community immediately reporters converged 
on the front entrance 
the man hadnt even seen his mother and four or five reporters 
were knocking on his door i said look fellows come over here 
and interview me 
even wellwishing neighbors created some problems although 
souter and rath said their support was appreciated 
he told me the other day that he parked his car at the post 
office to mail a package and it took him 45 minutes to get from his 
car to the window rath said people are warm and friendly and 
such but it gets wearing 
everyone in souters circle are happy that the attention is 
abating 
i think theres a feeling of enormous relief rath said 
this is a man who likes his work and the fact that he hasnt 
been able to work for the last 2 months has been hard 
once he goes back to work hell stay there eschewing the 
washington social scene that already has chosen him one of its most 
eligible bachelors rudman predicted 
he will be here as he was in new hampshire essentially 
extraordinarily hardworking he said 
if anybody in this city thinks that those phonies who send him 
those power invitations will get their hands on him they are in 
for one terrible disappointment said rudman whose dislike for 
the social whirl is well known 
as of monday at 5 pm when souter will take the first of 
two oaths of office rudman said he will essentially disappear 
as a person who is seen in the scene here in this city 
</TEXT>
