<TEXT>
east germany would have been 41 years old on 
sunday but few people found a reason to mark the birth of a nation 
that no longer exists 
the oncehallowed anniversary passed quietly with no lavish 
parades no mass protests for democracy and most significantly no 
east germany 
the former communist nation closed out its history wednesday by 
acceding to west germany 
lothar de maiziere the nations first and last freely elected 
leader said sunday was not a day of forced marches and ordered 
jubiliation but simply the first sunday of a united germany 
we have achieved freedom and democracy the former prime 
minister said in a statement we will protect these as precious 
commodities 
the soviet union formed the german democratic republic on oct 
7 1949 from the rubble of the nazi empire and installed a 
stalinist government 
for 40 years the anniversary was a national holiday marked by 
celebrations and parades that paid tribute to the nations history 
and its communist system 
last year however it became a flashpoint for the revolt that 
toppled the old regime and eventually opened the door to 
unification 
the protests that had been gathering steam in the weeks previous 
were given new impetus when soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev 
visited the country and told east german leader erich honecker to 
institute reforms 
life punishes whoever comes late he told honecker 
thousands protested on the date last year some shouting 
gorby help us less than two weeks later honecker was ousted 
a caretaker communist government opened the berlin wall and 
promised free elections 
de maizieres party was elected on a prounity platform and 
east germanys fate was sealed 
one of the few vestiges of the past was in view sunday as some 
of the activists who helped lead the democratic revolt kept up 
their vigil outside the former headquarters of the communist secret 
police in berlin 
the activists are trying to keep officials from the west from 
gaining control of the secret dossiers on 6 million people they 
say the files should remain on what was once east german land and 
be made available to the public 
officials confirmed saturday that west german investigators have 
begun examining the files to gather evidence to bring former secret 
police leaders to trial 
but there was little else reminiscent of the past the vast 
parking lot in front of the palace of the republic once the seat 
of the former communist parliament was turned over to an 
automobile show that charged passersby 310 to enter 
at the former communistrun old museum the national gallery 
of the gdr remained intact devoted to paintings and sculpture 
