<TEXT>
an untreatable fatal genetic disease thought 
confined to the descendants of eastern european jews has turned up 
in this heavily catholic community 
nobody knows how taysachs disease got here but it apparently 
is turning up at an even higher rate than among jews 
babies with taysachs develop normally until they are about 6 or 
7 months old after that they degenerate slowly but steadily 
taking years to die 
its so awful to sit and watch your child deteriorate said 
renee abshire whose daughter maigon died of taysachs less than 
two months after her third birthday 
she lived with constant pneumonia constant coughing mrs 
abshire said the last six months of her life id sit and cry 
mrs abshire 26 was checked twice during her pregnancy for 
deformities or hereditary problems in the developing fetus 
her obstetrician never checked for taysachs it didnt seem 
necessary testing for taysachs is routine in many jewish 
communities but renee and david abshire are fundamentalist 
christians and unaware of any jewish ancestors 
talking with doctors around southwest louisiana mrs abshire 
now president of the local taysachs amp allied diseases association 
chapter found three other children with taysachs 
none was jewish and in three of the four cases including hers 
at least one parent had attended iota high school 
the connection made this cajun town of 1200 people something of 
a genetic ground zero three cases werent an epidemic but were 
enough to make people wonder how a rogue gene a destroyer of 
children had slipped into their bloodlines 
in this small a community youd never see this many cases so 
you can say its kind of an explosion said dr michael quinn a 
crowley pediatrician who treats children from iota it has to be 
that someone moved there years and years ago and two families had 
the gene and through intermarriage right in the iota area thats 
where the disease is concentrated 
dr emmanuel shapira a tulane medical center geneticist 
checked the blood from 230 townspeople in july more people wanted 
to be tested but shapira ran out of test kits the results he 
said were astonishing 
its very very high at a level to justify screening every 
couple that wants to have children he said as many as 5 
percent are going to be born with it 
he said 17 of the people he screened carried the gene that can 
cause taysachs thats 74 percent or nearly double the carrier 
rate among jews and about 20 times the rate among the entire 
population 
a child with taysachs lacks a crucial enzyme the body needs to 
break down fatty deposits in brain and nerve cells 
without the enzyme deposits accumulate disastrously the 
nervous system stops working muscle tone vanishes respiratory 
problems develop it is always fatal usually before the age of 5 
the disease is on a gene carried by about 4 percent of all jews 
and about a tenth that rate in the entire population there is no 
reliable estimate of the number of cases said marjorie epstein a 
spokeswoman for the national taysachs amp allied diseases 
association 
carrier couples who try to have children face another tough 
decision what to do if a prenatal test shows the fetus has 
taysachs abortion is frowned upon in this conservative 
overwhelmingly catholic section of louisiana 
the abshires have decided not to try to conceive again 
the hardest decision for me if i got pregnant again would be 
to terminate my pregnancy said mrs abshire i know of someone 
who had to do that god didnt set me down here to judge her who 
am i to judge her when i know what taysachs did to me and my 
husband what we went through 
</TEXT>
