<TEXT>
sale of the state phone company 
entel was postponed for up to one month sunday because the 
government could not agree to final terms with the us and 
european buyers 
after insisting for a year the sale would take place oct 8 to 
coincide with the birthday of party founder juan domingo peron 
president carlos menem said the transfer now will take place from 
15 days to a month from now 
a main obstacle is entels rate structure public works minister 
jose dromi told reporters during breaks in negotiations that lasted 
all weekend 
thirtyone percent of customers bills is taxed to support the 
national pension fund purchasers want the tax removed or the 
government to hike rates an equivalent amount before they take 
over 
also customers and many politicians are outraged by the 42 
percent rate increase that took effect sept 24 bringing hikes 
this year to near 2400 percent 
that assures the private companies a profitability much higher 
than stipulated by the bid specifications said peronist party 
sen liliana gurdulich chairwoman of the bicameral state reform 
committee that monitors the sale of public companies 
sale of the empresa nacional de telecomunicaciones is one of the 
biggest privatization projects in the world 
the aging moneylosing system of 3 million lines and 46000 
employees is to be divided into two sections 
investors have agreed to pay 594 million in cash and notes and 
retire 5 billion of argentinas foreign debt for 60 percent of 
entel 
the debtequity swap is a way for the government to reduce a 66 
billion foreign debt and for banks to get at least some value for 
loans trading on secondary markets as low as 12 cents on the 
dollar 
problems cropped up last thursday when a group led by usbased 
manufacturers hanover bank and philadelphiabased telephone company 
bell atlantic corp failed to meet a deadline to make the down 
payment for entels northern section and dropped out 
that group was replaced by italian and french telecommunications 
companies stet and cables and radio respectively usbased jp 
morgan amp co bank and the argentine ship and bank conglomerate 
perez companc 
another group led by spains telecommunications company 
telefonica usbased citibank and the argentine construction and 
engineering company techint won the bid for the southern section 
but reportedly wont pay and take over until stet does likewise 
